					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The idea is interesting, but I think that $40 is a bit too much for a cart that can only run NROM and MMC1 games.
<br />
<br />I still didn't understand exactly how this work though. Does your program get written to the Flash ROM or is that chip only for booting? If the Flash is used for the program I think that the cart doesn't qualify it for intense use (i.e. emulator replacement), so the only advantage I see over standard socketed carts + EPROM programmer is the direct PC connection that eliminates the chip swapping.</div>

