						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">blargg wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Aren't most of those guys crazy about expansion chips?</div><br />Simple: disable the CIC on your NES, then use stop-n-swop and put in a cartridge with the audio expansion chip of your preference, and run the NSF player with that.</div>
<br />Only $0000-$07FF and possibly $6000-$7FFF can be loaded after a stop-n-swop. Your NSF would have to copy itself down there, and this location is off limits to APU DMC.</div>

