				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Well, not necessarily Tepples. Once swopped, presumably a loader program will still be in the 2k WRAM of the NES, and then one can draw more data off the serial cable for playback and use it immediately, discarding it. One would not have to store everything.
<br />
<br />EDIT: correct me if I'm wrong Blargg, but if NSF playback is all that is desired, once the player is in the WRAM then you could run without a cartridge at all, and simply play NSF's being fed through the controller port.</div>

